{"lemma":"طِبِّ","slug":"طِبِّ","root":"ط.ب.ب","root_slug":"ط-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26261","","n26268","n26269","n26270"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَبَّ (ṭabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"medicine (field of study)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to treat medically"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَبَّ (ṭabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَبَّ (ṭabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tˤibː/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26261","headword_ar":"طَبَّ","root":"Tb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, Msb, K, TA,) agreeably with analogy in the case of a trans. reduplicative verb [like this], (TA,) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) which is irregular, (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * Msb, K, * TA) [and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tub~N","text_ar":"طُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also accord. to the O and K, but, accord. to the Msb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the subst. from this verb, and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tub~N","text_ar":"طُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is likewise a simple subst.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He treated medically, therapeutically,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curatively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, * Msb, K, *) another person (O, Msb) [or the body, and in like manner the soul: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below]. ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabyota","text_ar":"طَبيْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, (S, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tababota","text_ar":"طَبَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, (O, K,) [third pers. of each"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~a","text_ar":"طَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and, accord. to analogy, the aor. of the former is"},{"kind":"text","text":", and of the latter"},{"kind":"text","text":", but from what follows it seems probable that one says also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabubota","text_ar":"طَبُبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the same sense, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", unless"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tababota","text_ar":"طَبَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taTut~u","text_ar":"تَطُتُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an irreg. aor.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"becamest a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabiyt","text_ar":"طَبِيت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"physician"},{"kind":"text","text":"], not having been such. (S, O, K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino kunota *aA Tub~K faTub~a liEayonayoka","text_ar":"اـِنْ كُنْتَ ذَا طُبٍّ فَطُبَّ لِعَيْنَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, and so in copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liEayonika","text_ar":"لِعَيْنِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in other copies of the K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"linafosika","text_ar":"لِنَفْسِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISk, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*A Tab~K","text_ar":"ذا طَبٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*A Tib~K","text_ar":"ذا طِبٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTab~a","text_ar":"فَطَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTib~a","text_ar":"فَطِبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If thou be a possessor of the art,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"science, of physic, be a physician to thine eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thine eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thyself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning, begin by rectifying thyself. (ISk, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 902.]) ―         -b3-  And [hence]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~a","text_ar":"طَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted with skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expertness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and in this sense likewise the second pers. is probably"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabibota","text_ar":"طَبِبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tababota","text_ar":"طَبَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabubota","text_ar":"طَبُبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which last the inf. n. is app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaAbapN","text_ar":"طَبَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in one of the phrases here following:] so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiSonaEohu SanoEapa mano Tab~a limano Hab~a","text_ar":"اِصْنَعْهُ صَنْعَةَ مَنْ طَبَّ لِمَنْ حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou it in the manner of him who acts with skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expertness, for him whom he loves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a prov., relating to the accomplishing an object of want skilfully and well. (El-Ahmar, TA. [See also Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 717.]) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEomalo fiY h`*aA Eamala mano Tab~a limano Hab~a","text_ar":"اِعْمَلْ فِى هٰذَا عَمَلَ مَنْ طَبَّ لِمَنْ حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do thou, in this, the deed of him who acts with skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expertness, for him whom he loves"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, Msb, * TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano Hab~a Tab~a","text_ar":"مَنْ حَبَّ طَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Meyd,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^aHab~a","text_ar":"مَنْ اَحَبَّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~a","text_ar":"طَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who loves is skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercises art,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ingenuity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for him whom he loves: (Meyd:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who loves executes affairs with deliberateness and gentleness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [That one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabubota","text_ar":"طَبُبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabibota","text_ar":"طَبِبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tababota","text_ar":"طَبَبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", seems to be indicated by the fact that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaAbapN","text_ar":"طَبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as an inf. n., is thus written, in a copy of the KL in my possession, and expl. as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"medical art:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Golius, however, appears to have found it written, in a copy of the same work, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbapN","text_ar":"طِبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is agreeable with analogy as inf. n. of a verb of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"significant of an art, and is probably correct: Freytag mentions the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaAy^ibu","text_ar":"طَبَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying medical"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1820},{"kind":"text","text":"arts, on the authority of the Deewán of the Hudhalees.] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~ahu","text_ar":"طَبَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He enchanted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascinated him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tub~a","text_ar":"طُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was enchanted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascinated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.]) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~a Als~iqaA='a","text_ar":"طَبَّ السِّقَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~bhu","text_ar":"طبّبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed to denote muchness, (S, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tTobiybN","text_ar":"تطْبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He covered the seams of the water-skin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk-skin, with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbap","text_ar":"طِبَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (S, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~a Alxuraza","text_ar":"طَبَّ الخُرَزَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he covered the seams with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbap","text_ar":"طِبَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA) [and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmazaAdap","text_ar":"المَزَادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~abati","text_ar":"طَبَّبَتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a girl, or young woman,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of skin called"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbN","text_ar":"طِبَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAbapN","text_ar":"طِبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the place of junction"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of each"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the two extremities of the loop-shaped handles of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though she rectified the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mzAdp","text_ar":"مزادة"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereby. (A.)"}],"source_refs":["O","Msb","K","TA","S","ISk","Meyd"]},{"entry_id":"n26268","headword_ar":"طَبٌّ","root":"Tb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  It is also an inf. n. used as an epithet: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And, (S, A, Msb, K,) as such, i. e. an inf. n. used as an epithet, or by original application, but the former is app. the case, and some have mentioned likewise ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tb~N","text_ar":"طبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tub~N","text_ar":"طُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing knowledge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Msb, TA,) respecting a thing, or of a thing; (A, Msb, TA;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and (TA) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expert;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, S, K:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gentle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, TA;) and so too ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Tab~N bika*aA","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ طَبٌّ بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is knowing with regard to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is one possessing knowledge of, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu Tab~uwna","text_ar":"القَوْمُ طَبُّونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as some relate it, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu maA A^aTab~uwna","text_ar":"القَوْمُ مَا اَطَبُّونَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", is a prov.: the former means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, are knowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skilful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [Meyd says,] I know not any way in which the latter is explainable unless ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTab~u","text_ar":"اَطَبُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axo$anu","text_ar":"اَخْشَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xa$inN","text_ar":"خَشِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"a connective. (Meyd.) To a man who offered to cure the [so-called] seal, or stamp, of the prophetic office between the Prophet's shoulder-blades, asserting himself to be a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tabiyb","text_ar":"طَبِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or physician], the Prophet replied, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybuhaA","text_ar":"طَبِيبُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*~iY xalaqahaA","text_ar":"الَّذِّى خَلَقَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has knowledge respecting it is He who created it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And El-Marrár El-Fak'asee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tadiynu limazoruwrK A_ilaY janobi HaloqapK\n                      \n                     ↓ \n      mina Al$~ibohi saw~aAhaA birifoqK TabiybuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She obeys a plaited nose-rein attached to the side of a ring of brass, the skilful maker of which has fashioned it with gentleness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, L:) i. e. the she-camel of which he speaks obeys her rein that is tied to her nose-ring of brass. (L.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHolN Tab~N","text_ar":"فَحْلٌ طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A stallion"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expert in covering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that knows the she-camel that is pregnant from her that is not, and her that desires the stallion from her that is covered without desire, and the motion of the fœtus in the womb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is gentle, and does not injure the female that he covers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN Tab~N","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A camel that is mindful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"careful, as to the place of his foot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where to tread with it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that does not place his foot save where he sees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K","MF","TA","T","L"]},{"entry_id":"n26269","headword_ar":"طُبٌّ","root":"Tb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26270","headword_ar":"طِبٌّ","root":"Tb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tub~N","text_ar":"طُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Medical, therapeutical,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curative, treatment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * O, * Msb, K, *) of the body, [i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"physicking"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof,] (A, K,) and likewise of the soul. (K.) ―         -b2-  [And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowledge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaruba Tib~N","text_ar":"قَرُبَ طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowledge is near"},{"kind":"text","text":"], or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaruba","text_ar":"قَرُبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~FA","text_ar":"طِبًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Meyd, O, K, TA,) with the noun in the accus. case, as a specificative, (TA,) like the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma rajulFA","text_ar":"نِعْمَ رَجُلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Meyd, O, TA,) is a prove.: originally said by a woman to a man who asked her an indecent question which he was himself about to resolve: (Meyd, O, K, TA:) it is like the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota EalaY Almujar~abi","text_ar":"اَنْتَ عَلَى المُجَرَّبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (Meyd, TA:) and is related on the authority of Ibn-Háni. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Skill,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expertness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, ISd, Meyd, TA.) This is said in the T to be the primary signification. (TA. [But see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabiybN","text_ar":"طَبِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness; gentle treatment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Enchantment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fascination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA: but only"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is mentioned in this sense in the S and O:) used in this sense as ominating cure. (AO, O, * TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tib~N","text_ar":"طِبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Desire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appetence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahowapN","text_ar":"شَهْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wish;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iraAdapN","text_ar":"اـِرَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b7-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"State, condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aA^onN","text_ar":"شَاْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA^obN","text_ar":"دَاْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, TA:) [or by the latter of these two words may be meant what here follows:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"custom, habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA*aAka biTib~iY","text_ar":"مَاذَاكَ بِطِبِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is not my custom, habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, TA.) [See also another ex., in a verse (added here in the S and TA) which I have cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ino","text_ar":"اـِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", page 107, col. iii.]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tab~N","text_ar":"طَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","Msb","K","Meyd","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}